For installation, the dependencies can be obtained as follows.

Python dependencies can be installed via:
    cd <path/to/project/folder>
    pip install -r requirements.txt

For Ubuntu/Debian:
    sudo apt-get update
    sudo apt-get install cmake g++ libfftw3-dev libsndfile1-dev
    git clone https://github.com/zsiciarz/aquila.git
    cd aquila
    mkdir build
    cd build
    cmake ..
    make
    // SYSTEM-WIDE INSTALLATION:
        sudo make install
    // LOCAL INSTALLATION:
        cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/path/to/your/project/ ..
        make
        make install

For Fedora:
    sudo dnf install cmake gcc-c++ fftw-devel libsndfile-devel
    git clone https://github.com/zsiciarz/aquila.git
    cd aquila
    mkdir build
    cd build
    cmake ..
    make
    // SYSTEM-WIDE INSTALLATION:
        sudo make install
    // LOCAL INSTALLATION:
        cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/path/to/your/project/ ..
        make
        make install


For macOS (using Homebrew):
    brew install cmake fftw libsndfile
    git clone https://github.com/zsiciarz/aquila.git
    cd aquila
    mkdir build
    cd build
    cmake ..
    make
    // SYSTEM-WIDE INSTALLATION:
        sudo make install
    // LOCAL INSTALLATION:
        cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/path/to/your/project/ ..
        make
        make install

For Windows:
    git clone https://github.com/microsoft/vcpkg.git
    cd vcpkg
    bootstrap-vcpkg.bat
    vcpkg install fftw3:x64-windows
    vcpkg install libsndfile:x64-windows
    vcpkg integrate install
    git clone https://github.com/zsiciarz/aquila.git
    cd aquila
    mkdir build
    cd build
    cmake -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=[path_to_vcpkg]/scripts/buildsystems/vcpkg.cmake ..

Then, once all required installs have been done, the project can be built with:
    make clean
    make

For the visualization Jupyter Notebook, you will need to run:
    pip install notebook
    cd src/vis